ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
How many repetitions of standing and sitting from a chair can the subject complete in the specified timeframe?
Specified timeframe for the chair rise task (in seconds)
How many high marches can the subject complete in the specified timeframe?
Specified timeframe for the knee raise task (in seconds)
Wii Balance Trial 1 reason for fail
Notes: 1 = Participant refused; 2 = Not attempted; 3 = Unable to attain position or cannot hold for at least 1 second

ElementDescription: Wii Balance Trial 1 number of seconds held position
Wii Balance Trial 2 reason for fail
Notes: 1 = Participant refused; 2 = Not attempted; 3 = Unable to attain position or cannot hold for at least 1 second

ElementDescription: Wii Balance Trial 2 number of seconds held position
Wii Balance Trial 1 When you completed the task with one foot, eyes open, how steady did you feel?
Wii Balance Trial 1 Did you do any of the following during the task?
Notes: 2 = Step off the platform; 3 =  Need to stop the task early (before 30 seconds had passed); 4 = Other
